                            <comment id="12901781" author="jukkaz" created="Tue, 24 Aug 2010 09:01:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In fact the format instances can also be static, we just need to protect them against concurrent access.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since the date formats are typically only accessed a few times per each parsed document, using normal synchronization shouldn&apos;t cause any lock contention.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See the attached patch for a proposed solution.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
